3 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Condition of grants -- disbursement of funds. (1) The disbursement of
4 grant funds for the projects specified in [section 1(2) and (5)] is subject to completion of the following conditions:
5 (a) The grant recipient shall document that other matching funds required for completion of the
6 project are firmly committed.
7 (b) The grant recipient must have a project management plan that is approved by the department
8 of commerce.
9 (c) The grant recipient must be in compliance with the auditing and reporting requirements
10 provided for in 2-7-503 and shall use a financial accounting system that the department of commerce can
11 reasonably ensure conforms to generally accepted accounting principles. Tribal governments shall comply with
12 auditing and reporting requirements provided for in 2 CFR 200.
13 (d) The grant recipient shall satisfactorily comply with all conditions described in the application’s
14 project summaries section of the Montana coal endowment program 2027 biennium project funding
15 recommendations to the 69th legislature.
16 (e) The grant recipient shall satisfy other specific requirements considered necessary by the
17 department of commerce to accomplish the purpose of the project as evidenced by the application to the
18 department.
19 (f) Pursuant to 90-6-710(6), the grant recipient shall comply with all Montana coal endowment
20 program requirements as determined by the department of commerce in order to qualify for reimbursement of
21 project expenses.
22 (g) The grant recipient shall execute a grant agreement with the department of commerce.
23 (2) With the exception of bridges, all projects must adhere to the design standards required by the
