6 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Other powers and duties of department. (1) The department of
7 commerce shall disburse grant funds on a reimbursement basis as grant recipients incur eligible project
8 expenses.
9 (2) If actual project expenses are lower than the projected expense of the project, the department
10 may, at its discretion:
11 (a) reduce the amount of grant funds to be provided to grant recipients in proportion to all other
12 project funding sources; or
13 (b) reduce the amount of grant funds to be provided so that the grant recipient’s projected average
14 residential user rates do not become lower than their target rate as determined by the department.
15 (3) If the grant recipient obtains a greater amount of grant funds than was contained in the
16 Montana coal endowment program application, the department may reduce the amount of the Montana coal
17 endowment program grant funds to be provided to ensure that the grant recipient continues to meet the
18 threshold requirements contained in the program guidelines for receiving the larger Montana coal endowment
19 program grant.
